          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "But wait, West Midlands Police said the BMW M3 wagon was a “death-trap botched together.” They sure talk funny in the UK, but the claim is the car structurally was held together by tag welds, making it ready to crumple like a beer can in a collision. While further details about what made this vehicle so dangerous weren’t provided, we wouldn’t be surprised to learn it didn’t have airbags or a nanny cam installed. Won’t someone think of the children?",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
